Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    ############################################
    # 1. Install Python tooling and pytest
    ############################################
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        ca-certificates
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    ############################################
    # 2. Prepare initial filesystem state
    ############################################
    # Ensure the /home/user hierarchy exists
    mkdir -p /home/user/audit

    # Allow the runtime (non-root) user to create further files
    chmod 755 /home/user
    chmod 777 /home/user/audit

    # Create the source CSV with **exactly** the required content
    cat >/home/user/audit/source_permissions.csv <<'EOF'
path,user,group,perms
/etc/passwd,root,root,644
/etc/shadow,root,root,640
/var/log/syslog,syslog,adm,640
/home/user/.bashrc,user,user,600
/usr/bin/sudo,root,root,4755
/tmp/shared.txt,guest,guest,666
/var/www/html/index.html,www-data,www-data,644
EOF

    # Default read permissions are sufficient
    chmod 644 /home/user/audit/source_permissions.csv

%labels
    Author  = ChatGPT
    Purpose = Initial state for audit-permissions task (pytest pre-checks ready)

%help
    Container providing the starting environment for the “file-system permission
    audit” task.  Includes:
      • /home/user/audit/source_permissions.csv with the exact required content.
      • pytest installed for the grading engine.
    Students are expected to create /home/user/audit/perm_overview.log.